This paper discusses the use of blockchain technology and AI, which are both relevant to the categories of cs.CY (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of AI in the context of social credit systems, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of decentralized architecture, which is relevant to the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
